*Exercise 1
** Pseudocode
   Arguments:
     arr // the items we're comparing
     i //starting index
     j //ending index

   if (i == j - 1)
   {
      return (arr[i] > arr[i + 1] ? arr[i] : arr[i + 1]; 
   }

   //base case - return the max of 2 items i == j - 1 or list.size() == 2
   //split the list in half and call maximum on each half
